As the pure chalk is of a very unctuous consistency and extremely tenacious owing to 113 smoothness‚ it is sprinkled with a coat of black, to prevent the extreme whiteness of the chalk from imparting 3 11310 hue to the gold-solder. The yellow gold-solder is thought to derive its name from the plant yellow-weed, which is itself often pounded up with steel-blue and applied for painting instead of gold-solder, making a very inferior and counterfeit kind of colour.

XXVIII. Gold-solder is also used in medicine, mixed with wax and olive oil, for cleansing wounds; likewise applied dry by itself it dries wounds and draws them together. It is also given in cases of quinsy or asthma, to be taken as an electuary with honey.
